HEADWORD: Phalangist
<hw>Pha*lan"gist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any arboreal marsupial of the genus <gen>Phalangista</gen>. The
vulpine phalangist (<spn>Phalangista vulpina</spn>) is the largest
species, the full grown male being about two and a half feet long. It
has a large bushy tail.</def> <-- Spanish history -- member of the
Falange?? Sp.? -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

